<h3 class="wikiHeadline3" id="H-EasierToUseCDK"><a href="/2009/07/08/rich-faces-face-2-face-meeting-review#H-EasierToUseCDK">Easier to use CDK</a></h3>
<p class="wikiPara">
We are also going to streamline the CDK and remove all proprietary file formats to make it easier to work with.  With JSF 2.0 there are fewer artifacts required for component creation and we are following suit.  The new CDK will by more annotation and convention driven, as well integrate easier with tooling. 
</p>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> XHTML file to generate renderer</li>
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> Base component classes for functionality</li>
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> Optional XML configuration file</li>
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> No more proprietary file formats</li>
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> Better tool support </li>
</ul>

<p class="wikiPara">
[<a href="http://www.jboss.org/community/wiki/RichFaces40ComponentsDevelopmentKit" target="" class="regularLink">CDK Updates Wiki</a>]
</p>

<h3 class="wikiHeadline3" id="H-ComponentAndCodeReview"><a href="/2009/07/08/rich-faces-face-2-face-meeting-review#H-ComponentAndCodeReview">Component and Code Review</a></h3>
<p class="wikiPara">
We will also be going through the whole component library and reviewing each for functionality, consistency, and performance.  If it makes sense we'll combine components, or deprecate unneeded components and API.  If it is unavoidable we may remove component and code now.  This means changes to TLDs, XSDs, and APIs are possible.  As always there will be more information on this in the meeting minutes, wiki, and forums.  
</p>

